title: For Sale:  Threading & Cerakote services
postcontent:
Turn down & thread rifle barrel.  Extend & thread pistol barrel.  All threading work is done concentric to the bore, indicated off the lands in a 4-jaw chuck.  More precise than a factory threaded barrel and accurate enough for a very tight bore silencer with no fear of baffle strikes.  Custom thread protectors to match can be included.  Threaded barrel extensions are 416 stainless steel unless another material is requested.  Barrels are re-crowned.  All threads cut single point

Cerakote finishing - see some samples of my work below.  From simple one color coats to patterns or camo.  

I have a 9-5 but still faster turnaround than sending your work off.

Pictures - threading work from L to R: Beretta U22 Neos, Sig P229, Remington 700, Beretta 92.  Closeup of extended, threaded P229 9mm barrel.  Examples of some Cerakote projects.

This ad generates many questions so maybe this will help you out:

1.  How much does it cost?
A:  That depends.  Many factors.  For threading, what specifically do you want done?  Do you want a thread protector too?  For Cerakote, how many colors, which colors, any patterns, and am I detail stripping and reassembling your gun or are you?

For ballpark pricing.... to extend & thread a pistol barrel for something like a Beretta 92 or Sig P220 would be around $70 + $10 for a thread protector.  To take your fully assembled 1911 and Cerakote it in one solid color I have to special order would be around $200

2.  Can you do my AK-47?
A:  Short answer is no.  I won't remove/install a barrel on an AK type action - I just don't have the right press/tooling to do that.  If you want to do that yourself, I'll work on it.  But I'd need a stripped barrel to thread it.  I'd need a detail stripped AK to Cerakote it and you will need to do the full reassembly.

3.  How long does it take?
A:  Generally a week - 10 days.  Depends on how busy I am with my 'real job' and how much other work I have in front of yours.  If I have to order a Cerakote color I don't stock that adds time too.

4.  Can you Cerakote wood/plastic/polymer/etc?
A:  Yes.  Certain things like scopes require the high temp Cerakote which is air cured and not as durable as the heat cured, but they can be finished in Cerakote. 

5.  My gun is beat to hell.  Can you fix gouges, scratches, dents, etc?
A:  Maybe.  Very light scratches or scuffs will be removed by the blasting process that's part of the Cerakote prep.  Something deeper may be able to be filled.  I can make it look better, but depending on how far gone it is I won't promise to make it look new.  Cerakote is applied 1 mil (0.001") thick - it's not going to "fill in" or "hide" any defects.

6.  Can you custom match a color?
A: No.  Cerakote material is expensive and adding a little of this & a little of that until it's a perfect match - when cured - to something else would end up in a lot of time and material waste.  Check out NIC Industries website for all the colors offered & you'll find something real close to what you want.  I'll do a custom mix to lighten or darken a standard color.  I can also adjust the sheen on many colors to control how flat or glossy it comes out within the limitations of that particular color or mix.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Beretta 25 Auto Mod-21A
postcontent:
The Beretta 21A Bobcat is a small pocket-sized semi-automatic pistol designed by Beretta. Current models are manufactured in the Beretta U.S.A. facility in Accokeek, Maryland.
The Beretta 21A Bobcat is a simple blowback pistol with a double-action/single-action (DA/SA) trigger mechanism. It is fitted with a frame-mounted manual thumb safety. 
One defining feature of this pistol is the 'tip-up' barrel. The barrel pivots on a pin under the muzzle so that the chamber may be loaded with the slide in the closed position. This simplifies loading, unloading, and checking load status. Finish is matt black with small amount of wear on edges.

title: For Sale:  Adams Arms complete ar-15 piston upper unfired
postcontent:
Carbine length complete Adams Arms piston upper that I have not fired. Put it on your ar-15 lower and you are ready to go. I have a complete lower to add to it so you have a complete rifle for $900 and this include a 30 round magpul pmag. Face to face in the Des Moines area.

Specs


This Adams Arms AR-15 A3 Base Carbine Gas Piston Upper Assembly is chambered in 5.56x45mm NATO and comes ready to fire right out of the box after installation onto any standard AR-15 lower receiver. This Base Carbine upper comes equipped with a 16" melonite-finished barrel, A2 flash hider, bolt carrier group, charging handle, picatinny rail gas block, delta ring assembly and a set of polymer M4-style handguards. Additional features include a forged A3 flat-top configuration that's ready to accept the shooter's choice of optic and/or rear iron sight, M4 feed ramps to help ensure reliable feeding and functioning during rapid strings of fire, and a carbine length gas system. 

The upper's barrel has been finished inside and out with Adams Arms' proprietary QPQ Melonite treatment that bonds with the metal on a molecular level. Also referred to as salt bath nitriding, this treatment produces an extremely hard, slick surface on steel that resists carbon adhesion and increases corrosion resistance, extending a barrel's service life by reducing the friction produced inside the bore upon firing for a net decrease in bore surface wear over time. Nitriding converts the barrel steel's surface without any build-up, retaining all of the benefits of traditional chrome lining without suffering the accuracy degradation commonly encountered due to uneven application of chrome inside the barrel's bore. The end result is a barrel that's capable of producing accuracy on par with a match stainless steel tube, while also exhibiting the longevity and resilience of a chrome lined, mil-spec barrel. 

All Adams Arms uppers feature a short stroke gas piston operating system, which prevents hot gas and debris from being directed back into the action upon firing. The result is a rifle that runs cooler, cleaner and more reliably than those utilizing a standard direct gas impingement system of operation. To ensure that damage doesn't occur to the buffer tube from carrier tilt, the bolt carrier is equipped with enlarged "skis" to help guide it into the receiver extension. The bolt carrier's solid steel, 1-piece construction incorporates an integral piston strike face to guarantee integrity over time, while the bolt assembly is spring loaded for proper lock-up and to help reduce bolt bounce and cam pin wear. All piston components are finished in QPQ Melonite for corrosion resistance and easy cleaning/maintenance. 

Specifications:

Gas System Length: Carbine, Short Stroke Piston Operated

Two years ago it was illegal to hunt in Indiana with a rifle like this.
 Last year Indiana changed the casing length to 1.8 inches.  I have a gunsmith
 CF Gunworks LLC  that took  the 350 Remington Magnum  and shortened that casing to 1.8 inches
 Which is what this cartridge now is. You can’t  buy this ammo or the gun ,they 
 have to be custom made which is why they are expensive. The .357 and .44 magnums are just another example of Indiana Deer Legal cartridges that you can use. This is a High Powered Rifle that has been modified to meet Indiana specs and requirements . This rifle is 100 % legal to hunt with in Indiana .
Don’t wait for Deer season to decide you want one, you won’t be able to. This is someone’s chance to own
a very nice Indiana Deer Legal High Powered Rifle of which only a hand full are available.

I have a custom built Remington Model 700 That was a 350 Remington Magnum
it has been shortened to 1.8 inch. Indiana Deer Legal casing
the factory barrel has been bedded and set back to shorten the chamber.
It comes with Redding Dies that have been ground to match. 
I have brass and about 30rds of ammo that was made by C F Gunworks.
It is toped off with a leupold 3x9.
This rifle killed 3 deer at over 300yds this past season. It is amazing!!
I would like $1600 with scope or $1400 without.

This Rifle was custom built to Indiana Specs!!!!! And is referred to as a 350 JR
 This cartridge is modeled after the Remington 350 Magnum. They shorten the case
 to 1.8 inches, I took a picture so you can see the cartridge, bullet is 200grn
and clearly meets Indiana guide lines. I hope this helps with the confusion. 
Certain rifles like the .357 magnum or .44 magnum can be bought at walmart
and are perfectly legal. Indiana says you can't go below .357 magnum. This rifle can't
be bought at WalMart they have to be custom made which the price reflects
